[Like many communicable diseases, canine influenza is passed around
easily in a social setting.

It is a serious disease and owners should pay particular attention to
their animal's health as this disease can be fairly rapid in its
progression and medical intervention is needed sooner rather than
later. Please take the precaution to vaccinate your pet. Vaccines can
be life saving!

For more information on canine influenza the moderator comments in the
references below (the see also list) provide interesting information.
